{"lemma":"عِشْرِينَ","slug":"عِشْرِينَ","root":"ع.ش.ر","root_slug":"ع-ش-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ش-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عِشْرُون","root":"عشر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","num"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29201"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%B4%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"num","gloss":"twenty","examples":[{"text":"إِنْ يَكُنْ مِنْكُمْ عِشْرُونَ صَابِرُونَ يَغْلِبُوا مِائَتَيْنِ","english":"If there are twenty among you who are steadfast, they can overpower two hundred."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"twentieth","examples":[{"text":"اَلْقَرْنُ الْعِشْرُون","english":"the twentieth century"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʿiśrū-. Compare Hebrew עֶשְׂרִים (ʿeśrīm), Aramaic עֶסְרִין (ʿesrīn) and Ugaritic 𐎓𐎌𐎗𐎎 (ʿšrm)."},"ipa":["/ʕiʃ.ruː.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29201","headword_ar":"عِشْرُونَ","root":"E$r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Twenty; twice ten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) applied alike to a masc. and a fem.: (Msb:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oruwna","text_ar":"عِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulFA","text_ar":"رَجُلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Twenty men"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oruwna A@moraA^apF","text_ar":"عِشْرُونَ ا@مْرَاَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Twenty women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the noun following it being in the accus. case as a specificative]: (TA:) it is decl. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like a pl. formed by the addition of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) and when you prefix it to another noun, making it to govern the latter in the gen. case, you drop the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oruw zayodK","text_ar":"عِشْرُو زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The twenty of Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oruwka","text_ar":"عِشْرُوكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy twenty"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, O, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$uriY~","text_ar":"عِشُرِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My twenty"},{"kind":"text","text":"], changing the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in this last case], because of the letter following it, and these incorporating: (S, O:) so says Ks; but most disallow this mode of prefixing in the case of a decimal number [of this kind], (Msb.) [It signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Twentieth."},{"kind":"text","text":"] It is not a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arapN","text_ar":"عَشَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in a copy of the S and in the O and in the TA.) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$orN","text_ar":"عَشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in another copy of the S,) [or perhaps the right reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$orN","text_ar":"عِشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as may be inferred from what will be presently added: but first it should be observed that if it were pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arapN","text_ar":"عَشَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$orN","text_ar":"عَشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it would signify at least three times ten: some hold it to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$orN","text_ar":"عِشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", saying, (TA.) as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$orN","text_ar":"عِشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies camels' coming to water on the ninth day, they do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oraAni","text_ar":"عِشْرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for twenty], but they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oruwna","text_ar":"عِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yuqalo Ei$orayoni waqaAluwA","text_ar":"لَمْ يُقَلْ عِشْرَيْنِ وَقَالُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oriyna","text_ar":"عِشْرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the correct reading seems to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo","text_ar":"لَمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaquwluwA","text_ar":"يَقُولُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":": TA: [in the CK it is more incorrect,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lm","text_ar":"لم"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yql Ei$oriyna wqAlwA Ei$orayoni","text_ar":"يقل عِشْرِينَ وقالوا عِشْرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) making eighteen days to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oraAni","text_ar":"عِشْرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the nineteenth and twentieth a portion of the third"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$or","text_ar":"عِشْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so, [regarding the portion as a whole,] forming the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oruwna","text_ar":"عِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, * TA;) agreeably with a well-known license, which allows the calling two and a part of the third a pl: (TA:) this is the opinion of Kh and IDrd and some others: but J and most of the lexicologists hold that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oruwna","text_ar":"عِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arapN","text_ar":"عَشَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$orN","text_ar":"عِشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor of any other word, and their opinion I hold to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applying as it does to the other similar nouns of number. (MF.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","TA","S","O"]}]}}